<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,404,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Herdman" authorityYear="1881" box="[324,546,404,428]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pyriformis">
<emphasis box="[324,546,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Molgula pyriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles the closely related species 
<taxonomicName box="[986,1222,404,428]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malvinensis">
<emphasis box="[986,1222,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Molgula malvinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ärnbäck-Christie- 
<bibRefCitation author="Arnback-Christie-Linde, A." box="[151,288,439,464]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref12112" refString="Arnback-Christie-Linde, A. (1938) Ascidiacea. Part 2. Further zoological Results of the Swedish Antarctic Expedition, 3 (4), 1 - 54." type="journal article" year="1938">Linde, 1938</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Traustedt, 1883" authorityName="Traustedt" authorityYear="1883" box="[347,775,439,464]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis box="[347,586,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Molgula occidentalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Traustedt, M. P. A." box="[595,775,439,464]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="108 - 136" refId="ref15357" refString="Traustedt, M. P. A. (1883) Vestindiske Ascidiae Simplices, Anden Afdeling. Molgulidae og Cynthiadae. Uidenskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk Naturhistorisk Forening ann. 1882, 108 - 136." type="journal article" year="1883">Traustedt, 1883</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Millar, R. H." box="[946,1102,439,464]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 160" refId="ref13509" refString="Millar, R. H. (1960) Ascidiacea. Discovery Reports, 30, 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1960">Millar (1960)</bibRefCitation>
, the main characteristics that separate them rely on the structure of the gonads, the shape of the intestinal loop and the dorsal tubercle opening. On the distinction between 
<taxonomicName box="[456,626,512,536]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malvinensis">
<emphasis box="[456,626,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. malvinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority=", Monniot &amp; Monniot (1976)" authorityName=", Monniot &amp; Monniot" authorityYear="1976" box="[679,1154,511,536]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pyriformis">
<emphasis box="[679,832,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. pyriformis</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Monniot, F. &amp; Monniot, C." box="[845,1154,511,536]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="671 - 680" refId="ref14010" refString="Monniot, F. &amp; Monniot, C. (1976) Quelques ascidies bathyales et abyssales du Sud Est Atlantique. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle Zoologie, 387 (269), 671 - 680." type="journal article" year="1976">Monniot &amp; Monniot (1976)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
agreed, claiming that the fundamental difference was found on the structure of the gonads (with 
<taxonomicName box="[998,1172,548,572]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malvinensis">
<emphasis box="[998,1172,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. malvinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presenting more male follicles on each gonad). However, on the revision of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Monniot, C. &amp; Monniot, F." box="[887,1183,583,608]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 168" refId="ref13783" refString="Monniot, C. &amp; Monniot, F. (1983) Ascidies antarctiques et subantarctiques: Morphologie et Biogeographie. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 125, 1 - 168." type="journal article" year="1983">Monniot &amp; Monniot 1983</bibRefCitation>
), the authors proposed instead the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName box="[430,600,620,644]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malvinensis">
<emphasis box="[430,600,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. malvinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Monniot &amp; Monniot" authorityYear="1976" box="[662,816,620,644]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pyriformis">
<emphasis box="[662,816,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. pyriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Subsequent sampling in the SW Atlantic enabled us to reject the latter proposition and support the decision of maintaining both as separate species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Taverna, A." box="[1192,1364,656,680]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refId="ref15235" refString="Taverna, A. (2013) Riqueza de ascidias de la Plataforma de Tierra del Fuego, colectadas durante la campana CONCACEN II del BO &quot; Puerto Deseado &quot;. Tesis de grado, Universidad Nacional de Cordoba, Argentina, 60 pp." type="book" year="2013">Taverna (2013)</bibRefCitation>
found six individuals which were identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[619,791,692,716]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malvinensis">
<emphasis box="[619,791,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. malvinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in an area close to its 
<typeStatus box="[1059,1107,693,717]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
location (
<collectingCountry box="[1224,1328,692,717]" name="Falkland Islands" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Malvinas</collectingCountry>
/ 
<collectingCountry name="Falkland Islands" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Falkland Islands</collectingCountry>
) and in a similar depth range (
<quantity box="[615,739,727,752]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.65" metricValueMax="12.8" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="96.5" valueMax="128.0" valueMin="65.0">65–128 m</quantity>
). Additionally, all of our specimens present the characters mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Millar, R. H." box="[313,465,764,789]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 160" refId="ref13509" refString="Millar, R. H. (1960) Ascidiacea. Discovery Reports, 30, 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1960">Millar (1960)</bibRefCitation>
as belonging to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Monniot &amp; Monniot" authorityYear="1976" box="[654,808,764,788]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pyriformis">
<emphasis box="[654,808,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. pyriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our specimens were also found in an area close to the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,800,824]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
locality of the latter (off 
<collectingRegion box="[478,631,799,824]" country="Argentina" name="Ciudad Autonoma de Buenos Aires" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Buenos Aires</collectingRegion>
) and in a similar depth range (
<quantity box="[968,1114,800,824]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.985" metricValueMax="10.97" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="598.5" valueMax="1097.0" valueMin="100.0">100–1097 m</quantity>
). In this way, we believe that the range of distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Monniot &amp; Monniot" authorityYear="1976" box="[483,642,836,860]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pyriformis">
<emphasis box="[483,642,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. pyriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the north of 
<collectingCountry box="[988,1147,836,861]" name="Argentina" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">the Argentine</collectingCountry>
Sea, while the range of distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[326,500,872,896]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malvinensis">
<emphasis box="[326,500,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. malvinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
extends from the south of 
<collectingCountry box="[826,982,871,896]" name="Argentina" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">the Argentine</collectingCountry>
Sea to the north of the South 
<collectingCountry name="United Kingdom" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Orkney Islands</collectingCountry>
. Thus, the only specimen found in the Southern Ocean classified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Monniot &amp; Monniot" authorityYear="1976" box="[1002,1157,908,932]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pyriformis">
<emphasis box="[1002,1157,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. pyriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Monniot, C. &amp; Monniot, F." pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 168" refId="ref13783" refString="Monniot, C. &amp; Monniot, F. (1983) Ascidies antarctiques et subantarctiques: Morphologie et Biogeographie. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 125, 1 - 168." type="journal article" year="1983">Monniot &amp; Monniot, 1983</bibRefCitation>
, might belong to 
<taxonomicName box="[405,575,944,968]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Molgula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stolidobranchia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malvinensis">
<emphasis box="[405,575,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. malvinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
